text: The 2005–06 Israeli Noar Leumit League was the 12th season since its introduction in 1994 as the top-tier football in Israel for teenagers between the ages 18–20. Hapoel Haifa won the title, whilst Hapoel Kfar Saba and Hapoel Jerusaelm were relegated. ==Final table== ==External links== *Noar Premier League 05-06 One.co.il Category:Israeli Noar Premier League seasons Youth
